review_blob: Absolutely amazing, big bold flavor, with a nice clean bite on the finish that invites another sip

I first would like to say that i think that just because Point doesnt typically make "flashy" beers that it isnt considered a good brewery. They make very very solid beers that taste very traditional to the specific styles that they brew. As far as this beer specifically, I loved their approch. They made a very nice "session" style IPA. Good hop presense but not over the top, gives a hophead a good show and is still able to be approchable to a newbie. The galaxy hops add a nice grapefruit/passionfruit citric flavor that is really nice. and for the price i cant think of another IPA that you can get for $7 a 6pk that i would rather have.

Really nice balance between sweetness and mouthfeel. Had a really curvy sort of heavyness, deffinatly present but not truly heavy. Sweetness was kinda the same way deffinatly present but not sugary or overly carmely. Usually not a huge scotch ale fan but like all styles of beer the really good ones make you forget all the ones you didnt care for.
Really nice double IPA has all the hoppy goodness that you pay for when purchasing a double or imperial IPA. great use of centennial hops and pleanty of them!

Great smooth quality to this beer has a wonderful creamyness to it but really not overly sweet either which i hae experinced in other beers of this style. also not overly nutty as some beers also have. If your brown fan i would highly recommend this one, I know ill be back for more.

This is a perfect everyday kinda beer. Has a great hop flavor, mild on the alcohol, hoppy enough to be intersting but not so hoppy that you couldnt sit down on a nice day and have a six pack (which i did). and again they did such a great job of showcasing one specific hop (Cascade). I can see why this is considered their flagship beer.

Had this on tap at Stolps Stein Haus in La Crosse WI. Really nice stout had some interesting (I dont want to say licorice but I cant think of a better word) flavors that I thought were fairly unique to this beer.

Couldnt like this beer anymore! Great use of trappist yeast to really balance out the finish on this beer. Got a ton of great hoppy flavor with some really nice citric notes to it but the yeast really smooths out the finish in a really nice and refeshing way. Thank you Ale Asylum keep them coming!

I love love love how they showcase the amarillo hops in this beer! Great balance this brewery is known for using a lot of hops so I was really happy that while very hoppy they didnt make something that made you feel like your chewing hops as you drink it.
Another home run from the boys in Madison. Such a great balance, although aggresivly hopped for an amber it still has enough malt backbone to really shine. Great beer and well made.
Great beer from a great brewery!! Has a wonderful bitter chocolate flavor and a coffee like quiality that is really really nice.
